						<div class="postbody">Well I guess I mean that it's pretty much impossible to avoid piracy of the torrent kind unless you really just can't use it without owning a legitimate copy. For example, a trombone can't be torrented (yeah yeah, there's midi crap, but whatever), but something like a NES game is pretty much completely vulnerable to piracy. That was pretty much my only point (well, Bananmos's point kind of).
<br />
<br />But most PCs aren't powerful enough to emulate PS3 games, I don't think. It may be possible to burn PS3 games onto DVDs, but it probably won't be possible to just emulate them.</div>

					
